episodes.title: Treehouse of Horror XV
episodes.plot: Ned gains the power to foresee people's deaths; Maggie is shrunk inside a vitamin capsule and swallowed; Eliza Simpson and her sidekick hunt down a murderer.

episodes.title: All's Fair in Oven War
episodes.plot: Homer buys Marge a new kitchen, and Marge likes cooking in the new kitchen so much she attends the Ovenfresh Bakeoff.

episodes.title: Sleeping with the Enemy
episodes.plot: Because she thinks her own children do not appreciate her anymore, Marge becomes a mother figure for Nelson.

episodes.title: She Used to Be My Girl
episodes.plot: Marge becomes jealous when Lisa begins idolizing her old high school friend, Chloe Talbot, a famous reporter.

episodes.title: Fat Man and Little Boy
episodes.plot: Bart begins designing T-shirt slogans, and his T-shirts become very popular among the citizens of Springfield.

episodes.title: Midnight Rx
episodes.plot: Homer goes to Canada with Apu and Ned to purchase Grampa's medication, but the three have problems getting home because the border guard thinks Apu is a terrorist.

episodes.title: Mommie Beerest
episodes.plot: Homer gives Moe an enormous amount of money so he doesn't have to close down.

episodes.title: Homer and Ned's Hail Mary Pass
episodes.plot: A video of Homer dancing becomes so popular that all major sports players hires Homer to design celebration dances for them.

episodes.title: Pranksta Rap
episodes.plot: Bart went to a rap concert Marge told him not to go to. In order to avoid punishment from Marge, he makes Marge and Homer believe he has been kidnapped.

episodes.title: There's Something About Marrying
episodes.plot: A townsperson comes out of the closet when Springfield legalized same-sex marriages in a plot to bolster tourism; Homer uses the Internet to become a minister.

episodes.title: On a Clear Day I Can't See My Sister
episodes.plot: After bullying her, Bart is restricted by court order to come too close to Lisa.

episodes.title: Goo Goo Gai Pan
episodes.plot: Selma decides to adopt a child, so the whole family goes to China.

episodes.title: Mobile Homer
episodes.plot: After a garage-cleaning accident, Marge wants Homer to get life insurance. Instead, the family gets an RV.

episodes.title: The Seven-Beer Snitch
episodes.plot: Springfield builds an opera house, but since no-one attends it they convert it into a prison. Old and forgotten laws are used to fill the prison, and therefore Homer goes to jail for kicking a can five times in a row. In jail, Homer becomes a snitch

episodes.title: Future-Drama
episodes.plot: Bart and Lisa see into the future where their lives have changed.

episodes.title: Don't Fear the Roofer
episodes.plot: Homer meets a new friend, Ray the Roofer, but gets confined to a mental institution when his friends and family think he made him up.

episodes.title: The Heartbroke Kid
episodes.plot: Bart starts living on food from the new candy machine in school only, but he becomes so overweight that he has to go to a fat camp.

episodes.title: A Star Is Torn
episodes.plot: Lisa attends a singing competition for children, and Homer becomes her manager because of his skill to write songs that the crowd loves.

episodes.title: Thank God It's Doomsday
episodes.plot: Homer hears about the Rapture, and by using numerology to calculate when the Rapture is coming he learns that it is only one week away.

episodes.title: Home Away from Homer
episodes.plot: After Homer humiliates Ned Flanders, Ned, Rod, and Todd decides to leave Springfield and live in Humbleton, Pennsylvania.

episodes.title: The Father, the Son, and the Holy Guest Star
episodes.plot: Bart is expelled from Springfield Elementary, and Bart is therefore enrolled in St. Jerome's Catholic School.
